task.procedure:
&rolestepA;
Update the autofs map.
Add an entry for the diskette file system such as the following: pcfs -fstype=pcfs :/dev/diskette

&rolestepA;
Create an entry in the autofs map such as the following:/usr/local -ro,public bee:/export/share/local
The public option forces the public handle to be used. If the NFS server does not support a public file handle, the mount fails.

&rolestepA;
Create an autofs entry such as the following:/usr/local -ro nfs://bee/export/share/local
The service tries to use the public file handle on the NFS server. However, if the server does not support a public file handle, the MOUNT protocol is used.

&rolestepA;
Restart the NFS service on the server.
Type the following command.# svcadm restart network/nfs/server
